# Work tracking (ideas + Issues)

Keep designs and the build queue out of chat-only memory.

## Two homes

| Kind of knowledge | Where |
|-------------------|--------|
| Fleshed-out design (vision, mechanics, open questions, blocked-on) | `docs/ideas/<topic>.md` |
| Actionable build work (bugs, implementable chunks, prerequisites) | GitHub Issue |
| Current focus (short) | `docs/NOW.md` |

Do **not** leave a solid design only in the conversation. Do **not** open an Issue for every vague musing — park it as an idea first.

## When a chat designs something without shipping it

Before ending (or before switching topics):

1. Create or update `docs/ideas/<short-kebab>.md` from `docs/ideas/_template.md`
2. Set **Status** (`idea` / `designed` / …) and **Blocked on** if prerequisites exist
3. Add a row to `docs/ideas/README.md` index
4. Link the chat title / branch / PR in the idea file when useful

## When work becomes actionable

1. Open a GitHub Issue for the **next implementable chunk** (often a prerequisite, not the whole vision)
2. Link Issue ↔ idea file both ways
3. Set idea status to `building` when a branch is actively implementing it
4. Update `docs/NOW.md` Focus / Next / Blocked (keep it short)

## When shipping

1. Close the Issue via PR as usual
2. Set idea status to `shipped` (or leave a phase-2 section if only part landed)
3. Trim `docs/NOW.md` Focus

## Retroactive mining

Past agent chats are **not** reliable sources of truth. Do not pretend transcript scrapes are complete. Prefer: user memory → new idea stubs → Issues when ready.
